WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:05.126
Hey, good morning family. Praise the Lord. Thank you for joining me today.

00:00:05.127 --> 00:00:12.093
There is a lot going on again as usual, but I just wanted to say happy Palm Sunday.

00:00:12.094 --> 00:00:18.413
We have one week from today that we are able to celebrate the Lord Jesus Christ and his resurrection.

00:00:18.414 --> 00:00:23.594
What a time of the year it is! This is my favorite time of the year, y'all.

00:00:23.595 --> 00:00:37.490
I mean, whenever the spring is here, the grass is coming out, all the beautiful trees are budding, and all the birds are coming back from the south, I personally believe, other than fall, it doesn't get better than that.

00:00:37.491 --> 00:00:45.359
I love fall, too; I love the colors. But I'm excited about resurrection Sunday.

00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:59.999
We're going to pray for the protection over the people today for resurrection Sunday, that no terrorist attacks, no plots, and no plans of the evil one would come against us as we go into our houses of worship to worship our risen savior.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:06.193
I know that the enemy comes to kill, steal, and destroy, but we have power and authority over him.

00:01:06.194 --> 00:01:11.911
We're not going to allow, in the name of Jesus, any of that to happen in any places of the earth.

00:01:11.912 --> 00:01:23.330
The Lord warned us when I've told you all about praying over the churches in the Middle East, our brothers and sisters in the Middle East, praying over them that they would have safety in this time of worship.

00:01:23.331 --> 00:01:40.952
And even in the United States of America, I know that we keep things at bay as we take our authority, take communion, pray daily, and come before him boldly, taking our rightful place and seat next to him.

00:01:40.953 --> 00:01:47.917
I know a lot of people liked the tithing video. I made that; I try to be real with people, but you're not going to appease everybody.

00:01:47.918 --> 00:01:55.702
So, I'm just like, 'Whatever. If you like it, you like it; if you don't, you don't.'It's what we believe, it's how we live, and this is how I'll continue to live.

00:01:55.703 --> 00:02:06.559
And what I believe is that unless the Holy Spirit corrects me, I'm just going to keep on keeping on because I've been doing it for 20 years. So, it is what it is.

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:21.114
People ask me, 'Brandon, what do you believe?'So, we just tell you, 'Hey, this is where I'm at.'And if I told you the hundredfold ground, you'd get ticked off and wouldn't watch the channels anymore because I know some of the people you can't stand.

00:02:21.115 --> 00:02:29.750
So, we don't even tell you the hundredfold ground, but I know what the hundredfold ground is because I studied it.

00:02:29.751 --> 00:02:41.099
It took me years of sowing and praying and listening to the Holy Spirit and asking him what the hundredfold ground is.

00:02:41.100 --> 00:02:48.889
I found some nuggets, but that came through a lot of spiritual pressure.

00:02:48.890 --> 00:02:58.073
I try to hint around sometimes around these preachers that I know the hundredfold ground's on, and then I know the ones whose ground is bad ground.

00:02:58.075 --> 00:03:13.348
I say it's crap ground that doesn't grow anything at all. People really follow some of those folks and they go, 'Oh yeah, they're really good ground.'I say, 'No, that ground sucks.'I'm just being real. Probably not a good word to use, but it's just true.

00:03:13.349 --> 00:03:34.993
And you've got the one ground that's really good and they go, 'We can't stand them because they have jets and they have all this stuff.'Folks, I'll give you a hint on some things: if they are successful in ministry, the Bible says if you're faithful with little, God will make you ruler over much.

00:03:34.994 --> 00:03:41.488
So, God is the God of increase. He's the one that brings the increase on folks.

00:03:41.489 --> 00:03:48.914
And if they are walking in abundance, they've been faithful with what they have and God's giving them more.

00:03:48.915 --> 00:04:00.256
So if you see somebody who doesn't have much and their ministry isn't flourishing year after year and they're staying the same, they haven't passed the test.

00:04:00.257 --> 00:04:09.693
It takes you going from glory to glory, and you pass the test, and he gives you more like the talents.

00:04:09.694 --> 00:04:15.642
But you get mad and want to crucify the guy who has more and they go, 'Well, how much do they have?

00:04:15.643 --> 00:04:20.380
They have too much; they must have swindled it out of an old lady.'Folks, come on.

00:04:20.381 --> 00:04:29.390
God is the God of increase. So, you want to gravitate to the ground.

00:04:29.391 --> 00:04:35.962
If they've been in ministry—not like me, I've been in ministry for a year and a half going on two years.

00:04:35.963 --> 00:04:42.363
Two years, right? Wow, time goes fast. So I'm just a baby in this, just like a toddler.

00:04:42.364 --> 00:04:57.279
But if you've been in ministry for 30 years and you're still the same and you haven't changed and nothing's going from glory to glory and your capacity hasn't increased to be able to handle or reach more, you haven't passed the test.

00:04:57.280 --> 00:05:05.660
It doesn't make you bad; it just means you need to go through the refiner's fire so that you're able to handle more.

00:05:05.661 --> 00:05:11.705
Does that make sense, what I'm trying to tell you all? You see a lot of ministries that don't have any more anointing.

00:05:11.706 --> 00:05:15.630
They don't have any more presence. They don't have any more stuff going on for them.

00:05:15.631 --> 00:05:20.585
They keep going on the same way, going around the same mountain all the time.

00:05:20.586 --> 00:05:33.839
You look at them and then you give to their ground and you go, 'Oh, well, I understand.'But then you sow to the good ground that is blessed and you go, 'Wow,'and you instantaneously get a big harvest back.

00:05:33.840 --> 00:05:45.697
And I've learned to test the soil. I flow that way. I tell my wife all the time, 'Let's not go and give a whole bucket load of seed.

00:05:45.697 --> 00:05:57.795
Let's take $100 or $50 and sow it into that ground and see how long it takes.'And we'll call that in. It's not all on the minister, too.

00:05:57.796 --> 00:06:22.879
By the way, the Holy Spirit said this to me: 'Brandon, you're blaming the harvest solely on the minister, but the sower has part of it, too.'It's not all on the person in the soil; it's on the seed sower. So you need to know it's a half-and-half responsibility.

00:06:22.880 --> 00:06:41.273
You have to name your seed, you have to water your seed by watering it with the word, calling those things that be not as though they were, keeping strife out of your house, taking communion on a day-to-day basis, and sending your angels forth in the name of Jesus to bring forth your harvest.

00:06:41.274 --> 00:06:51.288
And if you're sitting there just idly by going, 'Well, I'm just waiting for my good truck to come in with all my goods on it.

00:06:51.289 --> 00:07:00.602
Where's my miracle package?'I told you the Bible says whatever you put your hands to will prosper.

00:07:00.603 --> 00:07:05.718
So if you've got to put your hand to something, you don't sit by with your thumb in your nose.

00:07:05.719 --> 00:07:11.572
You've got to go out and do something. Put your faith in action.

00:07:11.573 --> 00:07:16.156
Faith without works is dead. Now I sit there and go, 'Well, I'm just waiting.

00:07:16.157 --> 00:07:24.282
I want my angel to bring my sack of money.'I told you that's a miracle and that happens, but it's not something that happens all the time.

00:07:24.283 --> 00:07:31.235
I'd say more than what I've ever seen in my life, God says, 'Brandon, go out and get it, buddy.

00:07:31.236 --> 00:07:39.800
Take your hand to it and make it happen. But I will bless whatever you put your hands to.'Do something with your life.

00:07:39.801 --> 00:07:48.599
You're waiting so much for the ice cream truck to come by, but you've got to go out and get it.

00:07:48.600 --> 00:07:57.822
Go down to Blue Bell and get you some. I haven't had ice cream in a while; the Lord won't let me have it.

00:07:57.823 --> 00:08:06.284
So, I'm thinking about it right now. It's like, 'Oh, God, help me.'Just being real.

00:08:06.285 --> 00:08:18.959
I was thinking about my ice cream, but we're getting over that. Anyway, doing these videos... okay.

00:08:18.960 --> 00:08:26.552
So, when we see the ground and you're sowing into the ground, look at the fruit that the ground has.

00:08:26.553 --> 00:08:35.036
What's going on around their ministry? Is their ministry prospering? Is their ministry flourishing? Has God anointed them?

00:08:35.037 --> 00:08:42.334
If you see change and souls are coming in like Billy Graham, you know Billy Graham was good soil, right?

00:08:42.335 --> 00:08:46.879
He's not here anymore, so I can use him as an example. You won't throw eggs at me.

00:08:46.880 --> 00:08:54.389
Billy Graham's soil—I'm sure at that time, I never sowed into it—was probably very fertile ground because why?

00:08:54.390 --> 00:09:00.159
He was getting a lot of people born again and his ministry was exploding.

00:09:00.160 --> 00:09:03.912
It was like, "Wow, look at what's going on with Billy Graham.

00:09:03.913 --> 00:09:06.687
Everybody knew Billy Graham."He was a household name, right?

00:09:06.688 --> 00:09:18.578
So, if you see somebody and God is really touching them, try it. That's all I can say. Try it.

00:09:18.579 --> 00:09:30.295
And maybe, just maybe, if you keep your heart right and don't badmouth them, you sit there and think, "God, you're obviously touching this individual for a reason.

00:09:30.296 --> 00:09:41.359
Something's going on with it. I'm going to test the ground."Now, if you have some of these others whose ground is their ministry, they're the same.

00:09:41.360 --> 00:09:54.374
Their following hasn't changed. If it seems that everything around them is dying, then you have to go.

00:09:54.375 --> 00:10:14.143
There's nothing wrong with small churches, but if the church is not getting any growth, if it is not bringing anybody to get saved, if it's not baptizing, if it's not laying hands on the sick, if it's not casting out devils, I would consider why I'm going to church there.

00:10:14.144 --> 00:10:18.712
Does that make sense? You have to be careful where you're going.

00:10:18.713 --> 00:10:23.518
Don't go and put yourself in a church that's dead. They're not getting any outreach.

00:10:23.519 --> 00:10:28.224
They're not getting anybody saved. They're just there on a Sunday or Wednesday.

00:10:28.225 --> 00:10:41.525
They have a couple Bible studies and go home, and they're not really into expanding our tent and reaching the nations for Jesus because that's what we're there for anyway.

00:10:41.526 --> 00:10:56.533
I don't want to just have a feel-good sermon. Maybe have a potluck; some people have potlucks, you know, they'll have some tables or have some fried chicken or whatever, and they'll eat and have a little fellowship.

00:10:56.534 --> 00:11:08.713
And you walk away and think, "But did we get anybody new saved? Did we try?

00:11:08.714 --> 00:11:17.568
Did we help anybody?"Year after year, it's the same old thing.

00:11:17.569 --> 00:11:37.056
But if you're trying to expand your borders and you're letting the Holy Ghost flow, and you see people's lives changing—drug addicts or prostitutes or whatever—and they're getting their lives set free, then by all means, man, that's alive.

00:11:37.057 --> 00:11:47.836
I want to be where it's alive. I want to see people's lives changed from glory to glory where the Holy Ghost is allowed to move.

00:11:47.837 --> 00:11:54.676
It happens. There are churches like that. Collinsville is one.

00:11:54.677 --> 00:12:03.545
Pastor Candace and Chip let the Holy Ghost move, but there are some folks that won't.

00:12:03.546 --> 00:12:07.737
I'm trying to paint a picture that it's not all the soil's fault.

00:12:07.738 --> 00:12:14.289
You've got to call in your seed, you've got to water your seed, and you've got to be speaking.

00:12:14.290 --> 00:12:18.693
Don't be speaking double. A double-minded man is unstable in all his ways.

00:12:18.694 --> 00:12:23.518
You can't be saying, "Well, we're broke, busted, and disgusted.

00:12:23.519 --> 00:12:27.203
We're never going to get anything. We're always going to be poor.

00:12:27.204 --> 00:12:40.048
Grandma was poor, we're poor, and my kids are going to be poor."No, we are barrier breakers.

00:12:40.049 --> 00:12:44.879
Poverty stops with us. We're not having it ever again. We're not going to live in it.

00:12:44.880 --> 00:12:53.468
I am going to decree and declare that the blessing and the favor of God is on me, and that everything I put my hands to will prosper.

00:12:53.469 --> 00:12:59.777
Everything I do, Father, I'm anointed to do it, and you've appointed me for such a time as this.

00:12:59.778 --> 00:13:07.414
My angels are going out right now from the north, south, east, and west, and bringing my harvest in.

00:13:07.415 --> 00:13:16.319
I thank you, Holy Spirit, that you're bringing favor. Everywhere I go, I have favor. When I walk into a store, I have favor.

00:13:16.320 --> 00:13:24.002
Whenever I walk out of the store, I have favor because I'm blessed coming in, I'm blessed going out, I'm blessed in the city, and I'm blessed in the field.

00:13:24.003 --> 00:13:39.119
You've got to believe it, but you've got to say it out of your mouth. Stop that milly-mouthed talking.

00:13:39.120 --> 00:13:46.301
Life and death is in the power of your tongue and you're eating the fruit of what you've been saying.

00:13:46.302 --> 00:13:57.434
Remember that, ladies and gentlemen. As a man thinketh in his heart, so is he.

00:13:57.435 --> 00:14:13.565
The Bible says as a man thinketh in his heart, so is he. So don't take thoughts that contradict what you feel in your heart.

00:14:13.566 --> 00:14:24.474
Out of the abundance of the heart, the mouth speaks. The more you say it, the more you're going to reap it.

00:14:24.475 --> 00:14:31.411
And you have more power over your seed than just the bad ground is what the Holy Spirit said to me. You need to know that.

00:14:31.412 --> 00:14:56.577
He said, "Brenda, you can't just blame that on the preacher's ground."He said, "There's a lot of them that are out there saying out of their mouth, 'Well, I never get a harvest.'"You need to learn, because I've learned to watch my words.

00:14:56.578 --> 00:15:06.615
I've never, since I've been raising my son in the last 16 years, said poverty out of my mouth.

00:15:06.616 --> 00:15:23.417
We refuse to live by the curse of the law. I'm blessed because Deuteronomy 28 says so.

00:15:23.418 --> 00:15:29.317
I believe that Isaac planted in famine and reaped a hundredfold that same year.

00:15:29.318 --> 00:15:36.938
I believe that God is no respecter of persons and that what he did for Isaac, he'll do for me.

00:15:36.939 --> 00:15:46.879
Isaac sowed in famine. Genesis 26, one of my favorite chapters.

00:15:46.880 --> 00:15:52.558
Isaac sowed in famine, and that same year he reaped a hundredfold.

00:15:52.559 --> 00:15:59.481
So he sowed in famine. There was no rain, but God still blessed it.

00:15:59.482 --> 00:16:07.634
It's not all just about the soil; it's what you believe and what you say out of your mouth.

00:16:07.635 --> 00:16:13.359
Life and death is in the power of your tongue. So you have to take authority over your words.

00:16:13.360 --> 00:16:39.630
You need to take communion and call crop failure over every bad word you've said, over every idle word of poverty, lack, and milly-mouthed talk like, "Oh, we're never going to get out of this house."I always have the blessing on my life.

00:16:39.631 --> 00:16:47.399
Why? Because I believe in the covenant that God has given me. Greater is he that is in me than he that is in the world.

00:16:47.400 --> 00:16:51.722
And he's given me the ability and the power to get wealth with these hands.

00:16:51.723 --> 00:17:03.934
Show me, Holy Spirit, how to do it today. Give me wisdom on where I'm supposed to put my boat into motion.

00:17:03.935 --> 00:17:12.666
Faith without works is dead. And if you're not doing something to bring it forth, your faith is not working.

00:17:12.667 --> 00:17:22.673
You are snared by the words of your mouth, too. So it all works like that big motor; it all ticks together.

00:17:22.674 --> 00:17:30.840
And if you're not walking in love and you're walking in strife and you're doing all the things, you're putting a dam on the blessing coming into your household.

00:17:30.841 --> 00:17:36.304
And I always come before covenant with this communion all the time. That's why we have it everywhere.

00:17:36.305 --> 00:17:41.931
I got sacks of them everywhere because I believe in the power of the blood of Jesus.

00:17:41.932 --> 00:17:46.827
I believe in the power of the communion and what he did for me.

00:17:46.828 --> 00:18:13.553
This is all about it right now, ladies and gentlemen: Palm Sunday going into the crucifixion of Good Friday and saying, "Jesus, thank you for what you did for me and you delivered me from Deuteronomy 28 according to your word."He said in Galatians, "Christ has redeemed me from the curse of the law."And this is what he'd redeemed me from: Deuteronomy 28 and all those curses down below it.

00:18:13.554 --> 00:18:24.750
He redeemed me from every single one of those curses. Deuteronomy 28 says all those blessings will come upon those, and he redeemed me from every one of them.

00:18:24.751 --> 00:18:34.399
I'm not underneath the curse because Galatians says that Christ redeemed me from all the curses of Deuteronomy 28, ladies and gentlemen.

00:18:34.400 --> 00:18:38.133
And we don't have to walk in sickness. We don't have to walk in lack.

00:18:38.134 --> 00:18:43.236
We can walk in abundance. And that's why we have to speak and decree a thing out of our mouth.

00:18:43.237 --> 00:18:50.125
Say it because life and death is in the power of your tongue. And faith calls those things that be not as though they were.

00:18:50.126 --> 00:18:55.363
And you have to speak it out your mouth. You have to say it out your mouth: "I believe.

00:18:55.364 --> 00:19:02.190
I receive a million-dollar check in the name of Jesus."Stretch out there big—that's big to me.

00:19:02.191 --> 00:19:12.526
I'm believing for a $100,000 check. I believe. You say it out your mouth: "I believe for a $10,000 check."You may just be at a $500 level.

00:19:12.527 --> 00:19:17.351
That's fine. Or a $100 level. I believe for a $100 check. Say it out your mouth.

00:19:17.352 --> 00:19:23.678
And the more you say it, the more you believe it because your heart's going to start to change. You're going to start to change.

00:19:23.679 --> 00:19:30.983
It's like dumping in clean water: when you see the oil and the dirty water, you keep dumping in the clean, clean, clean, and eventually it keeps filtering.

00:19:30.984 --> 00:19:42.975
It'll filter all that mess out of you. The more the life, the more this lifegiving beautiful Bible, this beautiful word gets on the inside of you and it becomes real to you.

00:19:42.976 --> 00:19:53.980
The more you get this inside of you and you go from glory to glory, that pouring water filters all that trash out because this is life.

00:19:53.981 --> 00:19:59.279
And so the more you get it, the more you won't think that because you're renewing your mind to the word of God.

00:19:59.280 --> 00:20:06.040
You got to renew your mind. You got to think what this word says about you.

00:20:06.041 --> 00:20:12.558
I believe what the Bible says about me. I can have what the Bible says I can have.

00:20:12.559 --> 00:20:16.451
Just like John Osteen used to say, "I believe what the word of God says about me.

00:20:16.452 --> 00:20:20.972
I can have what the Bible says I have."I'm not going to be moved by what I see.

00:20:20.973 --> 00:20:24.690
I'm not moved by what I feel. I'm going to be moved by what the word of God says.

00:20:24.691 --> 00:20:27.739
That's what you got to do. And that's what you got to believe.

00:20:27.740 --> 00:20:33.599
So, like I said, you can't just sit there and say, "Well, it's all about the preacher."No, it's about you, too.

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:39.999
You got to say things out your mouth. That's right. Life and death is in the power of your tongue.

00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:46.685
Remember that. So, I don't know what got me off on that, but Holy Ghost, I guess, he wanted that to be said.

00:20:46.686 --> 00:20:50.710
He told me, he said, "Brandon, you're missing it. You got to say more than that.

00:20:50.711 --> 00:20:54.042
You got to say more than that, son. You got to say more than that.

00:20:54.043 --> 00:21:00.288
It's not just about planting in the good ground, but you got to water your seed."Just like a farmer, we got to believe for the rain.

00:21:00.289 --> 00:21:04.082
You got to believe for the rain and believe for fertilizer. You got to believe for all this stuff.

00:21:04.083 --> 00:21:09.090
We got to say it and then you got to believe it and then you receive it.

00:21:09.091 --> 00:21:17.545
Be discerning and look around you. What kind of fruit is happening?

00:21:17.546 --> 00:21:21.753
Whose lives are being changed? Because the Holy Spirit's in that.

00:21:21.754 --> 00:21:39.119
When you see people's lives being changed and they're not staying the same and you can look at them a year later and that baby Christian's getting the meat of the word and they're learning how to stand and have a backbone—my goodness, that has to be some good ground there.

00:21:39.120 --> 00:21:46.163
Does that make sense? Because if they're not, bottom line is, y'all, I want you to be blessed.

00:21:46.164 --> 00:21:51.634
I don't want you to struggle. I don't want you to live another day in poverty.

00:21:51.635 --> 00:21:55.505
I don't want you to live another day in sickness and disease.

00:21:55.506 --> 00:22:05.011
This is the most beautiful time of the year for you to have an inward-looking examination.

00:22:05.012 --> 00:22:12.609
Check yourself and say, "Where am I at right now with the Father? Where am I at with the blessing on my life?

00:22:12.610 --> 00:22:22.306
Where am I at with healing and not walking into disease and poverty and lack and not enough? Am I in overflow?

00:22:22.307 --> 00:22:33.033
Is there anything that I can do to increase in my life to change, to tweak some things?"Maybe just a little bit.

00:22:33.034 --> 00:22:39.298
No, nobody's perfect. None of us are. But I'm going to tell you, we all strive to be more like Jesus.

00:22:39.299 --> 00:22:45.752
It's all about looking at him and staying vertical and saying, "Jesus, I want to be more like you.

00:22:45.753 --> 00:22:56.558
I've got a long way to go, Father. But one day, I believe from going from glory to glory, I'm being more and more like you.

00:22:56.559 --> 00:23:03.078
Thank you, Lord. I receive it by grace."But we take this body and we lift it up before him.

00:23:03.079 --> 00:23:06.958
We thank him for Palm Sunday. We thank him for all that he's provided.

00:23:06.959 --> 00:23:13.794
Thank him for he set the captives free and that the seeds we've sown in the past, he said, will come to harvest at last.

00:23:13.795 --> 00:23:19.154
And there'll be an acceleration of seed time and harvest in these days ahead.

00:23:19.155 --> 00:23:25.377
Believe that. Believe it today. So, Father, we take this body right now in the name of Jesus.

00:23:25.378 --> 00:23:29.204
And we thank you, Lord, that you were wounded for our transgressions.

00:23:29.205 --> 00:23:34.781
You were bruised for our iniquities. The chastisement of our peace was upon you.

00:23:34.782 --> 00:23:42.177
And with your stripes, we are healed. And we take this body in the name of Jesus. And we thank you, Father.

00:23:42.178 --> 00:23:51.202
We thank you, Lord, that we don't have to be underneath the devil's boot no more because Jesus Christ paid the price for it all.

00:23:51.203 --> 00:23:58.716
And we receive it by faith in the name of Jesus. And we say it out our mouth: "I am healed by your stripes.

00:23:58.717 --> 00:24:09.397
I am delivered from poverty because you said you became poor that we might be rich."We take this body in the name of Jesus and we thank you, Lord.

00:24:09.398 --> 00:24:16.908
Lord, we take the blood. We thank you, Lord, for your sacrifice for all those stripes and all that.

00:24:16.909 --> 00:24:24.973
You said if we confess our sins, he is faithful and just to forgive us of our sins and cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

00:24:24.974 --> 00:24:33.520
Lord, we've messed up. Father, we thank you, Lord. Forgive me of my sins.

00:24:33.521 --> 00:24:40.312
